="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation & Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png" alt="USAA"><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><h1 class="brief-title">Days 91-120 - Scale the Learning</h1><div class="doc-section"><h2>Institutionalize what worked</h2><div class="plan-grid"><div class="plan-card"><h3>Standards</h3><ul><li>Codify proven review patterns, evidence requirements, and exception rules.</li><li>Preserve legitimate LOB variation with explicit boundaries.</li></ul></div><div class="plan-card"><h3>Platform strategy</h3><ul><li>Translate case evidence into tool-selection and platform-roadmap decisions.</li><li>Clarify where RPA, workflow, API integration, AI assistance, or process redesign fits.</li></ul></div><div class="plan-card"><h3>Value governance</h3><ul><li>Create a quarterly portfolio view connecting realized value, control quality, adoption, and maintenance burden.</li><li>Make hold, repair, standardize, and retire normal decisions.</li></ul></div><div class="plan-card"><h3>Capability</h3><ul><li>Define coaching, mentoring, and technical-development priorities for Process Engineers.</li><li>Develop internal reviewers and champions to avoid a single-point-of-expertise COE.</li></ul></div></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>120-day success evidence</h2><ul><li>Leaders can see why each priority automation is being redesigned, assisted, automated, standardized, held, or retired.</li><li>Process Engineers use a shared decision language without reducing the work to compliance paperwork.</li><li>Risk and control evidence is visible early enough to shape design.</li><li>Business cases have named baselines, owners, measurement plans, and maintenance economics.</li><li>At least one proven pattern is ready for broader reuse, and at least one weak candidate is stopped or reframed for defensible reasons.</li></ul></div><div class="doc-callout"><h2>Important boundary</h2><p>Specific case counts, timelines, and target measures must be set with USAA after learning portfolio complexity and regulatory obligations. This plan defines the operating sequence, not a fabricated internal commitment.</p></div><div class="doc-footer"><span>Independent candidate work product for USAA · github.com/russelldudek/USAA</span><span class="page-number">120-Day Plan · 3</span></div></section></main></body></html>